title: skillet beef ole
directions: Brown meat in a large, heavy skillet over medium heat.
Stir with a wooden spoon to break into small pieces.
Add onion, green pepper and red pepper.
Cook until vegetables are tender-crisp. Gently stir in salt, chili powder, basil, garlic, beans and corn. Simmer for 5 to 10 minutes to blend flavors.
Stir in some of the reserved bean liquid if you want to increase moistness.
Gently stir in the olives and parsley.
Heat through and serve with a green salad and French bread.
Serves 4.

title: buffalo chicken wings with blue cheese dipping sauce
directions: Melt the butter or margarine in a small saucepan.
Add hot sauce and remove from heat.
In a large pan or deep-fat fryer, heat 1 inch of oil to 375°.
Fry wings in batch without crowding until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towels. Brush wings with spicy butter and serve warm, with Blue Cheese Dipping Sauce.

title: sensational double layer pumpkin pie
directions: Mix cream cheese, 1 tablespoon half and half and sugar with a wire whisk until smooth.
Gently stir in whipped topping.
Spread on bottom of crust.

title: grandma's ginger cookies
directions: Beat eggs, sugar, shortening and molasses together until smooth. Add flour, cinnamon, ginger, soda and salt.
Mix all ingredients together until well blended.
Form mixture into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll in sugar and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
You can mash the balls or leave them round.
They will crack on top if left round.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Bring chicken stock to a boil and add celery, onion and broccoli.
Cook until vegetables are tender.
Reduce heat; add milk and cheese.
Make a thickening of the flour and some milk and add to soup until desired consistency.
Do not boil.

title: slaw or fruit salad dressing
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt. Add the beaten egg, vinegar and water and cook slowly. When mixture thickens, add 2 heaping teaspoons of yellow mustard and 2 tablespoons of margarine. Mix until butter melts. Store in refrigerator. Keeps for several weeks.

title: cracker crust pie
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy and add cream of tartar.
Beat until stiff.
Add sugar gradually and then add vanilla.
Mix crackers and nuts together.
Fold all together and pour into 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Cover with 1 cup cream whipped to which 1 small can crushed pineapple had been added.
Sprinkle generously with coconut.

title: e-z cornbread
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients in large bowl.
Add cornbread mix.
Stir until just blended.
Melt butter in a 9 x 13 pan.
Pour cornbread in with butter.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: kentucky pecan pie
directions: Mix ingredients well and pour into pie shell.
Bake in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: microwave meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Shape into one inch balls. Arrange in microwave-safe pan.
Cover with wax paper and microwave on High for 20 minutes.
Good hot or cold.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Combine egg yolks, salt and milk; mix well.
Place over low heat, stirring constantly until warm.
Combine sugar and flour, mixing well.
Gradually add to milk mixture, stirring constantly. Cook over low heat; stir until thickened.
Remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla and coconut.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add sugar; spread on top of pie.

title: oriental pot stickers
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Place 1 teaspoon in center of each wrapper.
Moisten edges with water; press together.
Flatten bottom and make each one stand upright.

title: date bread(diabetic)
directions: Sift together the flour, baking powder, salt, mace, cloves and nutmeg.
Add dates.
Combine eggs, milk, sweetener and shortening; add to dry ingredients.
Put in greased loaf pan (9 x 5-inch). Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 hours.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Add cut up vegetables, dressing and cheese.
Chill and serve.

title: easy spinach souffle
directions: Heat
oven to 400°.
Grease a 2-quart souffle dish.
In a saucepan, combine mayonnaise, flour, onion, salt, nutmeg and pepper;
stir
constantly over medium heat for 1 minute.
Stir in milk
until
smooth.
Stir	constantly,
cook until thick. Remove from heat.	Stir in spinach.
Beat in egg yolks.
In a small bowl,
beat egg whites with cream of tartar until stiff peaks form.
Gently
fold
into
spinach mixture.
Spoon into prepared dish.
Place
on
lowest
rack of oven.
Reduce oven temperature to	375°.
Bake
for
40 minutes until puffed and golden brown. Serve immediately.	Serves 4 to 6.

title: paradise pumpkin pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine softened cream cheese, sugar and vanilla, mixing until well blended.
Add egg; mix well.
Spread onto bottom of pastry shell.
Combine remaining ingredients; mix well.
Carefully pour over cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 5 minutes, or until done.
Cool.
Brush with maple syrup and garnish with nuts, if desired.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Mix ingredients as listed.
Mix well after each addition.
Fold in rhubarb last.
Pour in baking dish.
Mix 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 teaspoon cinnamon, 1/2 cup chopped nuts well.
Sprinkle over top of cake and cut into cake with knife.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine sugar, oats, flour and cinnamon.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Arrange half of the apple slices in buttered 8-inch square dish.
Sprinkle half the sugar mixture over the apples.
Top with remaining apples and the rest of the sugar mixture.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until apples are tender.

title: raspberry ice cream cake
directions: Mix chocolate wafers and melted butter.
Press in bottom of pan for crust.

Layer: (first) raspberry sherbet; (second) half brownie crumbs; (third) drizzle half chocolate syrup; (fourth) vanilla ice cream; (fifth) rest of brownie crumbs and (sixth) drizzle rest of chocolate syrup.
Freeze overnight.
Serve frozen.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In a large bowl mix together all dry ingredients.
In medium bowl beat eggs slightly.
Add oil, vanilla, raisins, carrots, apples and coconut.

title: nacho dip
directions: Layer in a large pie plate (start with the cream cheese). Microwave until cheese is melted, about 5 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: low-fat jello salad
directions: Dump all ingredients into a large mixing bowl.
Mix well. Chill and serve.

title: italian beef
directions: Cook 15 hours in a slow, 250°, oven.
Remove meat and shred it.
Place in broth, put in containers and freeze until ready to use.
Serve on hoagie buns.

title: lemon chicken pasta
directions: In a large skillet melt margarine; stir-fry chicken in butter until cooked.
Add onion and cook onion until tender, but still crunchy.
Add lemon juice, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook 1 more minute.
Toss with cooked noodles.

title: chocolate ripple pound cake
directions: In small saucepan, melt shortening; add cocoa, stirring until smooth.
Set aside.
Cream butter and gradually add sugar; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Beat well after each egg.
Add flour and vanilla, mixing well.
Remove 2 cups of batter.
Add chocolate mixture; stir until blended.

title: quick barbecue beef
directions: Combine all ingredients in large baking dish.
Cover and bake at 400° for 2 hours.
Serve over noodles.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix ingredients, saving 1/2 of onion rings to sprinkle on top after pouring into casserole.
Top with pats of oleo or butter and season with salt, pepper and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: corn bread
directions: Sift together in a large bowl the flour, cornmeal, salt, sugar and baking powder.
Add the milk and egg. Beat for 1 minute, then add the cooking oil or soft shortening.
Beat for 1 more minute. Place 2 teaspoons oil in an 8-inch cake pan.
Pour in batter.
Oil will rise, greasing pan. Bake in a 375° oven for 25 minutes. Split and toast any left.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix all together and place in a glass baking dish or place in mold.
Chill overnight.

title: cherry dessert salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together with the exception of the whipped topping. Top the salad with the topping. Refrigerate overnight.

title: apple oat muffins(low-fat and no sugar)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl mix the flours, oats, spices, salt and baking soda.
Add the chopped apple along with the apple juice concentrate and raisins.
Stir just enough to mix. Spoon batter into nonstick or lightly oil-sprayed muffin tins and bake for 25 minutes or until tops bounce back when pressed lightly.

title: betty's peanut brittle
directions: (The prettiest brittle is made with half light Karo and half dark.)
Put sugar, syrup, water and salt in pan and cook over low heat until sugar melts.
Add raw peanuts.
Don't stir; watch.

title: no bake chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix together in pan, sugar, cocoa, milk and butter.
Cook on medium heat until mixture forms ball.
Remove from heat and cool for 1 minute.
Add vanilla, salt, peanut butter and oatmeal.
Mix well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Cool.

title: scalloped corn supreme
directions: Heat corn and milk.
Gradually stir in egg.
Add next 4 ingredients and dash of pepper.
Mix well.
Pour into greased 8-inch round baking dish.
Top with buttered crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: quick divinity
directions: Boil sugar, water and salt until the mixture reaches the hard ball stage.
Place cream in bowl and pour in hot syrup.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix until the mixture becomes firm enough to drop by teaspoon on wax paper.

title: mexican rice
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine and add rice, onion, green pepper and garlic.
Cook, stirring, over low heat until rice is brown, then add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook over low heat until liquid is absorbed, about 35 to 40 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix in a bowl the flour, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar. Add eggs and oil. Beat well. Add carrots and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all and refrigerate overnight.
May add whipped topping, if desired.

title: grilled honey mustard chicken
directions: Mix salad dressing, honey and mustard.
Spread over chicken and grill approximately 10 minutes.
Turn chicken breasts.
Spread more mixture over chicken.
Grill another 10 to 15 minutes or until tender.
Serve with grilled green onions.

title: chili
directions: Brown onion in oil.
Add ground beef and brown.
Combine tomato sauce and spices together; add onion and beef.
Simmer for 30 minutes or longer, if desired.
If too thick, add another can of tomato sauce.
If you want chili and beans, add 1 can pinto beans.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Whisk together eggs, soda, buttermilk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Bring oleo, water and cocoa to a boil over medium heat.
Pour over egg and buttermilk mix.
Add flour mix.
Pour onto a greased and floured cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 20 minutes.

title: pistachio nut cake deluxe
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour Bundt cake pan.
(I also cut out a circle of wax paper to fit bottom of pan to prevent sticking).
Melt shortening.
Put all ingredients into food processor.
Now, add shortening and mix for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes. Batter will be thin.
Spoon into prepared pan.
Level with spoon. Bake for 50 to 55 minutes or until cake comes out clean.
Remove cake when pan is cool to the touch.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Place hamburger and onion in bottom of casserole dish. Place cream of mushroom soup on next layer, then vegetables and cream of celery soup. Evenly space Tater Tots on top of casserole. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: german pancakes
directions: Pour into hot skillet with touch of Pam.
Bake at 350° until raised up the sides of pan.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Blend rest in a bowl, then mix well.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Combine jello, pineapple and water.
Bring to a boil and cool.
Add cottage cheese and prepare Dream Whip.
Refrigerate. Can use any flavored jello for color and Cool Whip.

title: hot fudge sauce for ice cream
directions: Mix together in saucepan, flour, sugar and cocoa.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook on medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Serve over ice cream.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and garlic; drain.
Add sauce, tomatoes and spices.
Line bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with tortillas (torn in small pieces).
Pour in 1/2 meat mixture, another layer of tortillas and rest of meat mixture.
Add another layer of tortillas.
Mix soup and milk and pour over top.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10 .

title: spinach balls
directions: Mix first two ingredients in a large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into balls.
Place on cookie sheets and freeze. When ready to cook, place in a 350° oven and bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Enjoy!

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix spices, flour, salt and water well.
Add pumpkin and mix. Add slightly beaten eggs.
Stir in milk.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake at 450° for about 15 minutes, until crust is set. Then reduce heat to 300° and bake about 45 minutes longer or until inserted knife comes out clean.

title: pineapple pizza
directions: Spread cake mix onto thoroughly buttered pizza crust.
Place sliced pineapple into mix evenly.
Sprinkle sifted sugar over pizza.
Cook at 300° for about 10 minutes.

title: strawberry angel delight
directions: When cake is cooled, trim any brown crust.
Cut cake in 3 layers.
Prepare whipped topping as package directs, using low-fat milk.
Stir in yogurt, food coloring and half the strawberries.

title: oven barbecue ribs
directions: Divide ribs into serving pieces.
Place in roasting pan.
Lay onions on top and pour over them the sauce made from the remaining ingredients. Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours in moderate oven or until tender.
Remove cover for the last 20 minutes and
allow to brown.

title: zucchini jelly
directions: Grate squash.
Boil without water for 15 minutes until clear. Add sugar and lemon juice.
Boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and add apricot Jell-O.
Cool and freeze.

title: all american barbecue sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Saute onion and garlic until soft.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Cover and let stand for 1 hour for better flavors.
Cool and refrigerate for up to a week.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chocolate drop cookies
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
I frost cookies with melted Andes Mints.
Twenty-one mints for cookies in recipe.

title: cheddar-broccoli noodles
directions: In 3-quart saucepan over high heat, heat water to boiling. Add noodles and broccoli.
Return to boiling.
Reduce heat to low. Cover; cook 5 minutes or until noodles and broccoli are tender, stirring occasionally to separate noodles.
Stir in one seasoning packet; drain off most of liquid.
(Reserve remaining seasoning packet for another use.)
Add cheese soup, sour cream and pepper. Heat through, stirring occasionally.
Garnish with sweet red pepper, if desired.
Makes about 4 cups or 6 side dish servings. Prep time:
10 minutes.
Cook time:
15 minutes.
tags: Campbell's chicken flavor Ramen noodle soup

title: pepper soup
directions: Brown meat in vegetable oil.
Add sliced onions, cooking until they begin to soften.
Sprinkle enough flour on meat to coat when mixed.
Add all of remaining ingredients except mushrooms.
Simmer 1 1/2 hours or until meat is tender and pepper flakes have completely softened.
Add mushrooms 1/2 hour before serving.

title: grandma's cake
directions: Prepare cake mix as directed, adding mandarin oranges to the batter.
Bake as directed.
When cake has cooled, mix Cool Whip, vanilla pudding and crushed pineapple together.
Frost cake. Refrigerate.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir pudding mix, pineapple with juice, nuts and 1 cup marshmallows in a large bowl until blended. Gently stir in 1 tub whipped topping. Mix remaining tub of whipped topping and 2 cups marshmallows in a separate bowl. Reserve 1/2 for garnish. Spoon 1/2 of the pudding mixture in a large bowl. Top with remaining marshmallow mixture and remaining pudding mixture. Garnish with reserved marshmallow mixture, marshmallows and maraschino cherries,
Refrigerate. Makes about 16 servings.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.	Combine flour, salt,
baking
powder,
pudding mix, margarine, egg and milk. Beat for 2 minutes.
Pour batter into pie plate.
Drain peaches, keeping the juice.	Arrange peaches on top of batter. Combine cream
cheese,
cup of sugar and 3 tablespoons of peach juice.
Beat
for
minutes.
Spoon
over
peaches
to within 1-inch of edge of plate.
Combine 1 tablespoon of sugar with 1/2 teaspoon
of
cinnamon.
Sprinkle over top.
Bake at 350° for
30 to	35 minutes until golden brown.	Filling will appear soft. Cool.
Store in refrigerator.

title: stew casserole
directions: Lay stew meat in casserole first.
Layer celery, carrots, potatoes and onions (as many as you want).
Add salt.
Pour tomato juice over top and bake for 3 1/2 to 4 1/2 hours when vegetables are done.
Easy and tasty.

title: home pasta dough
directions: In 1 large bowl, combine 1 cup flour, 1/3 cup water and remaining ingredients.
Beat on low speed for 2 minutes, occasionally scraping bowl.
With wooden spoon, stir in enough additional flour to make a soft dough.

Turn on lightly floured surface and knead until smooth and not sticky, about 10 minutes. Divide dough into 5 sections and let set covered for 10 minutes. Roll dough out on floured surface or put through pasta machine. Cut into desired shapes.
Let dry or cook immediately.

title: pancakes
directions: Separate the eggs.
Mix together in no particular order the egg yolks, milk, flour, and sugar.
Melt butter and add to the mix. Blend egg whites until stiff.
Fold into mix gently.
Add baking powder. Now you're ready to make some good pancakes. Rich, fattening, and guaranteed to stick to your ribs.

title: blueberry vinegar
directions: Place blueberries in 2-quart crock or jar.
(Do not use plastic container.)
Pour vinegar over blueberries; mash berries slightly with wooden spoon or potato masher.
Let stand overnight. Strain vinegar into 1 1/2-quart saucepan, discarding berries. Stir in sugar.
Bring to boil; boil for 10 minutes.
Pour hot vinegar into clean, sterilized bottles or jars and cap with clean corks.
If you use jars, line lids with several layers of plastic wrap.
Refrigerate.
Yield: 1 quart vinegar.

title: barbecue
directions: Brown hamburger, onion, salt and pepper together.
Drain grease.
Add brown sugar, chili sauce and tomato soup.
Heat and serve on a hamburger bun.

title: herbed new potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in their jackets.
Peel and slice while warm. Sprinkle immediately with sugar and vinegar.
Add onion, salt, pepper and mayonnaise.
Toss gently.
Fold in herbs.
Best made in advance and refrigerated.
Garnish with a bouquet of dill or parsley and sliced, hard-cooked eggs, if desired.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: leigh's snickerdoodles
directions: Mix first three ingredients.
Stir together the rest of ingredients and add to first three ingredients.
Form dough into balls the size of walnuts.
Roll them in a mixture of 2 teaspoons of sugar and 1 1/2 teaspoons of cinnamon.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend all ingredients together with mixer until smooth and creamy.
Spread on cooled cake.

title: apple pizza
directions: Unwrap rolls and lay flat on a round or square pan. Lay out the apples. Drizzle the melted butter all over the apples and sprinkle cinnamon, brown sugar and Mozzarella cheese. Preheat the oven to 325° and bake for about 25 minutes.

title: company squash
directions: Cut and cook squash until tender.
Mash and add oil, bouillon cube, onion, egg, sour cream, salt and pepper.
Pour into prepared casserole dish.
Combine bread crumbs, shredded cheese and paprika; sprinkle over top of squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: shrimp and pasta
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Heat oil and margarine until melted.
Cook shrimp and garlic until shrimp is pink.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Toss pasta and shrimp mixture until pasta is coated. Add salt and pepper and top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: spanish slaw
directions: Mix together and refrigerate several hours before serving.

title: quiche with vegetables
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix together. Put in a greased quiche dish. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Chop onions
and potatoes and stir-fry.
Place layer of potatoes and
onions
and layer of cheese.	Mix milk and eggs; pour over
onion
mixture. Repeat layers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry punch
directions: Make syrup of sugar, water, cloves and cinnamon.
Boil 10 minutes. Strain syrup after cooling.
Mix fruit juices with syrup and chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale and sherbet. Makes a nice adult, nonalcoholic punch.

title: raspberry trifle
directions: Cover base of dish with sponge cake.
Drain fruit and save juice.
Place fruit on top of sponge cake.
Make Jell-O using fruit juice and water.
Pour onto sponge cake and allow to set. Make up custard and allow to cool. Pour on top of fruit, sponge cake and Jell-O.
Whip the cream and spread over the custard when set. Decorate with raspberries.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Add celery and onion to browned sausage.
Cook until tender, not brown.
Stir in soup, milk, rice, salt and mushrooms.

title: lonie pickard's b~b~q sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and boil 30 minutes slowly.

title: green grape sparkle
directions: Put ice cream scoops in individual bowls. Top with grapes. Pour drink over top.
May also be served from punch bowl.
Easy for children to make and deliciously refreshing to eat or drink!

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese and noodles.
Sprinkle with cheese and cover with noodles.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken and sausage jambalaya
directions: Boil chicken until done.
Cool and debone.
Cook vegetables until tender, then add tomatoes and sausage, Worcestershire sauce, salt, pepper and garlic salt.
Simmer about 10 minutes.
Add rice to chicken in a big pot and vegetables and sausage mixture. Cook all together with the broth for about 20 minutes.

title: homemade rolls
directions: Bring the first 4 ingredients to a boil. Cool to lukewarm. Add the eggs and yeast.
Wait 10 minutes. Add the flour.
Let rise double, then cut out with biscuit cutter and place in greased pan. Let rise and cook in medium oven at 400° for 16 to 20 minutes. Can be refrigerated after dough rises one time.

title: taco tureen
directions: Brown hamburg, onion and green pepper until meat is done. Pour off fat; add remaining ingredients.
Simmer until heated through.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients and beat on medium speed for 5 minutes.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Bake in greased and floured Bundt pan in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.
Let set 15 minutes, then turn out on cooling rack.
Frost when cool.

title: banana split
directions: Peel 1 side of banana.
Take 1/2 strip lengthwise out of banana.
Fill with marshmallows and chocolate chips.
Put peel back in place and wrap in tin foil. Bake at 350° for about 5 minutes.
Melt chocolate and marshmallows and let cool.
Eat.

title: french dressing
directions: Shake all ingredients in a tightly covered jar.
Refrigerate and shake before serving.

title: heavenly hash
directions: Mix all together lightly and refrigerate.

title: bowtie pasta with tomato bacon sauce
directions: Cook bacon, drain on paper towels.
Pour off all but 2 tbsp. of bacon grease.
In grease, cook onion until tender.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper, stirring to break up tomatoes. Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low, cover and simmer for 15 mins.

title: german shortcake
directions: Mix all ingredients except the pie filling and cinnamon. Work with your hands.
Spread in a 9
X 13 inch pan.
Cover with pie filling.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 to 45 minutes.
Beat 2 egg whites stiff with 2 Tbsp. sugar.
Add 2 Tbsp. butter and cinnamon.

title: chocolate fudge
directions: Cook sugar and evaporated milk for 12 minutes.
In large bowl, mix peanut butter, marshmallow, chocolate chips and margarine. Pour hot mixture over it and mix.
Set in refrigerator to cool.

title: pine bark
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil.
Layer saltines on foil.
Boil sugar and margarine for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake at 400° for 7 minutes.
Watch very carefully, it burns easily.
Take from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips on crackers.
Let set until they melt a little, then smooth out.
Put in refrigerator.
Let harden.
Break into pieces.

title: bob's pumpkin bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix with electric mixer.
Pour into 3 small bread pans or 2 large bread pans (grease pans).
Bake for 1 hour at 350° or until done.

title: no fail yeast rolls
directions: Combine margarine and 1 cup hot water.
Mix and add to butter mixture the eggs, sugar, salt and 1 cup cold water.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Add bread flour.
Mix well and store in a large bowl.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: pickled beans or sauerkraut
directions: Boil water, vinegar and salt.
Cool.
Cook beans, cool and drain.
Add the drained corn.
Mix and put in glass or stone container.
Pour vinegar mixture over.
Let stand for 4 days or until they are as sour as wanted.
Put in jars.
Cook in hot water bath for a few minutes to seal.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, cinnamon and sugar; mix well and set aside.
Combine eggs, oil and strawberries.
Add to dry ingredients, mixing well.
Pour batter into two greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: homemade ice cream
directions: Mix all ingredients except vanilla in saucepan.
Heat until little beads appear.
Remove from heat and add vanilla.
Mix well and pour into ice cream freezer.

title: russian-spiced tea
directions: Let water come to a boil and add tea bags.
Let steep 4 to 5 minutes.
Remove tea bags and add remaining ingredients.
Keep hot without boiling.
Run through a strainer before serving.
Serves about 18 to 25.

title: spinach chicken pasta
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions.
Cook chicken, cube and squeeze lemon juice over chicken.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: marinated pork
directions: Mix orange juice, ginger and garlic powder.
Pour over pork. Marinate overnight in refrigerator.
(Cook in hot air cooker for best results.)
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°, then for 20 minutes at 320°.
Turn and marinate occasionally with sauce.
Check and cook longer, if desired.

title: lizzies
directions: The use of a candy thermometer to measure the temperature accurately and to prevent under or overcooking your candy is strongly recommended.
The boiling temperature indicates the concentration of the solution of your candy.
The higher the concentration, the longer it is cooked and the higher the temperature becomes.
That's why it is so important to use a candy thermometer.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco, eggs and flavorings.
In another bowl, combine flour, salt and baking powder.
Pour in creamed mixture and add all other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for one hour or until done.

title: liz's vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and serve with favorite raw vegetables. Chill thoroughly before serving.

title: marinated roast pork loin
directions: Place pork loin in large glass or plastic container.
Whisk together rest of the ingredients to make the marinade.
Pour on top of pork.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: starlight mint surprise cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream the butter. Gradually add sugar and brown sugar; cream well.
Add unbeaten eggs, water and vanilla; beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients. Gradually mix thoroughly.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: swiss steak
directions: Cut steak into serving sizes; salt, pepper and roll in flour. Fry steak until brown; pour off excess grease.
Add onion rings (that you have sliced and separated).
Add tomatoes that have been blended.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: mock italian cream cake
directions: Cut cookies in half lengthwise.
Cover bottom of 12 x 9-inch pan with sliced cookies.
Cook vanilla pudding according to package directions, adding 1 tablespoon rum.
While still hot, pour over cookie layer.
Add another cookie layer.
Repeat with chocolate pudding.
Add another cookie layer.
Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with nuts, jimmies or cherries.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: burger's chocolate pies
directions: Shift flour, cocoa, sugar together, mix well.
Add egg yolks slowly.
Add evaporated milk and mix well.
Add milk and water. Cook on medium heat.
Stirring constantly.
Add butter and vanilla flavoring when getting thick.
Pour into pie shells.

title: key lime pie
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Beat egg yolks in a medium mixing bowl. Pour in condensed milk, stirring constantly.
Add lime juice and rind. Add food coloring; stir until blended.
Pour mixture into graham cracker crust.
Place pie in oven and bake 15 minutes. Transfer to rack; let cool.
Spread Cool Whip on cooled pie.

title: christmas special fruit cake
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients together and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients; pour over fruit and nut mixture and stir until well coated.
Beat 3 eggs until foamy and pour into mixture.
Stir well.
Spoon in 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan that is greased and lined with wax paper.
Bake 1 hour and 45 minutes at 300°.
Cool 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: cabbage lasagna(low-fat recipe)
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and green pepper. Drain well. Add sauce.
In
a large casserole, sprayed with nonstick cooking spray, layer cabbage, meat, cheese and mushrooms.
Cover and bake at 350° until cabbage is tender, about 1 hour.
Great dish if you love cabbage.

title: cream of corn soup
directions: Melt butter in a large pot over medium heat.
Add onion and celery.
Cook 10 minutes.
Stir often.
Add creamed corn, milk and pepper.
Cook 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Serves 6.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Put sugar, corn syrup, 1/2 cup water, salt and peanuts in 2-quart microwaveproof bowl or casserole.
Cook on High (maximum power) for 5 minutes; stir.
Cook on High for 13 to 15 minutes or until the syrup separates into threads.
This is the hard crack stage or 300° on a candy thermometer.
Check temperature with thermometer several times during the last few minutes.
(Do not leave thermometer in oven while cooking.)
Stir in butter, soda and vanilla just until light and bubbly.
Pour over buttered cookie sheet.
Spread.
Cool and break into pieces.

title: creamy cauliflower
directions: Cook cut up cauliflower until done.
Mix mayonnaise and mustard.
Put cauliflower in casserole dish.
Cover top with mayonnaise mixture.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook in 350° oven until cheese melts.

title: sweet-sour beets
directions: Combine sugar, vinegar, beet juice, bay leaves and cloves in a saucepan.
Bring mixture to a boil, then pour over onions and beets.
Cover and chill.
Onions take on the beet color and the mixture keeps well.

title: barbecue cups
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease 12-cup muffin pan and set aside.

title: party cheese balls
directions: Combine 2 (8 ounce) jars or packages sharp cheese spread, 2 cups of natural cheese, Blue cheese and grated onion.
Beat until smooth.
Shape into 2 balls.
Chill thoroughly.
One plain and one garnished with nuts.
Chill again, then serve.

title: zesty zucchini saute
directions: In a large skillet over medium-high heat, melt butter and oil. When hot, add zucchini, garlic, parsley and basil.
Saute until tender-crisp (7 minutes).
Season with salt and pepper.
Serves 4.

title: terry's mango pie
directions: Mix milk, juice and pulp with 6 ounces Cool Whip.
Blend well; pour into crust.
Spread remaining 2 ounces of topping over top. Refrigerate until firm.
May be frozen and served frozen.

title: vegetable soup with rice
directions: Soak beans overnight in cold water to cover; drain.
Combine bacon, onion and butter in a large saucepan and cook over medium heat until golden, stirring frequently.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix yeast with warm water and sugar; let set.
Sift flour and let set.
Pour boiling water over shortening.
Mix salt and 1/2 cup sugar and eggs together.
Mix boiling water and shortening with sugar and egg mixture.
Add 1/2 of the flour, mixed yeast, water and sugar.
Add remaining flour.
The amount of flour may vary depending on the weather.
Divide in half and let set out 3 hours in a warm place to rise.
If placed in refrigerator, roll out and let rise one hour before cooking.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes or until brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Add stuffing; mix well.
Mix remaining ingredients in large bowl.
In small baking dish, add 1/2 of stuffing mixture; press firmly.
Add squash mixture, then add remaining stuffing mix to top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: spaghetti and sauerkraut
directions: Brown and drain sausage; add spaghetti and sauerkraut.
Salt and pepper.
Cook until hot and blended.

title: potato gnocchi(no fat)
directions: Steam the potatoes in their skins until tender.
When cool enough to handle, peel and mash.
Immediately add the flour and the salt.
Knead on a lightly floured surface until smooth.
If dough sticks, add a little more flour.
Form into rolls about as thick as your thumb.
Cut into 3/4-inch sections and press down with a fork.
Add the gnocchi and boil until they rise to the top (about 5 minutes).
Add the gnocchi in several batches.
Drain and place in a warm bowl.
Mix the gnocchi with just enough sauce to completely coat them.
Extra sauce can be added by each person, according to their taste.

title: cheese toast
directions: Get a piece of bread.
Put cheese on top.
Put it in the toaster oven until cheese is melted, then eat it.

title: masoods' kheema biryani(saffron rice with ground lamb)
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In small bowl, drop saffron threads in; add boiling water and soak for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, in heavy saucepan, bring 2 cups of water to boil.
Pour in rice and add salt.
Cook uncovered for 10 minutes.
Strain and put rice aside. Separately, heat oil.
Add onions, cumin seed and salt; stir for 3 or 4 minutes.
Add turmeric and cumin for 1 minute, then add lamb. When cooked, add fresh coriander.
Heat remaining 1/4 cup oil and in 4-quart casserole, stir in fennel seed and rice until coated. Spread 1/3 of rice mixture on bottom of casserole.
Layer 1/2 the saffron mixture and 1/2 lamb mixture.
Spread the other half of the rice over the lamb and add the meat and then add the remaining rice mixture.
Put rest of saffron over mixture.
Add chicken stock and pour in casserole and bring to boil over high heat. Cover casserole with sheet of foil and fold down.

Set lid on top of foil and bake in the middle of the oven for 25 minutes, or until rice is tender and all the liquid is absorbed in casserole. Fluff the rice with fork and serve the biryani directly from the casserole or serve on platter.

title: apple pudding
directions: Beat the eggs until fluffy.
Add the sugar, then the other dry ingredients.
Add apples and nuts.
Bake in well-greased 8-inch pan 50 minutes at 325°.

title: pinch cake
directions: Melt margarine.
Add brown sugar and cinnamon; mix well.
Take thawed bread and make into dough balls.
Mix dough balls into margarine mixture.
Put dipped dough balls in greased Bundt pan. When all done, pour remaining margarine mix over dough balls in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings. Preparation time:
35 minutes.

title: punch for fifty
directions: Chill ginger ale, orange soda and pineapple juice.
Put ice cream and sherbet in large punch bowl.
Pour chilled ginger ale, soda and pineapple juice over top and stir.

title: shrimp victoria
directions: Saute shrimp and onion in
margarine
for
5 to 10 minutes, until shrimp is pink and tender.
Add mushrooms and cook 5 more minutes.
Sprinkle
in
flour, salt and cayenne pepper. Stir in sour cream and
cook
gently
for
minutes (do not boil). Serve over white rice.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: mayonnaise biscuits
directions: Mix and put in muffin tin.
Bake at 400° for about 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Brown ground meat until it loses its pink color, then drain. Add onion and peppers to meat mixture and saute for about 5 minutes; set aside.
Mix cornbread mix into an iron skillet that has been heated with oil in oven.
Pour meat mixture over cornbread mix.
Top with grated cheese.
Pour remaining mix over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: peanut butter roll
directions: Mix the cream cheese and sugar together.
Save enough sugar to roll candy in.
Roll out and spread with peanut butter.
Roll up and chill before slicing.

title: wet cake
directions: Don't use mixer and don't grease pan.

title: judy carlton's hobo beans
directions: Combine the first 8 ingredients.
Simmer 20 minutes. Add the beans and bake 1 hour at 325°, covered, then 1 hour, uncovered.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add next 5 ingredients and mix well. Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana bran muffins
directions: Mix well. Pour into muffin cups, using 1/3 cup per cup.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Yields 24 large muffins.

title: tortilla soup
directions: Note:
1 can green chilies, chopped, may be substituted for jalapenos.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix well and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 425°.
Bake, until done, at 350° (about 1 hour).

title: round steak with onions and sour cream
directions: Saute steak with onions and butter.
Simmer 20 minutes.
Add sour cream, mushrooms and flour.
Simmer 5 more minutes.

title: cheesy nachos
directions: Spread tortilla chips over large platter.
In medium saucepan, combine undiluted soup, salsa and 3 tablespoons of water.
Heat over low heat to simmering, stirring occasionally.
Allow to simmer 1 minute.
Pour mixture over chips.
Sprinkle with scallions and olives.
Serves 8.

title: chili con carne
directions: Use a 2 1/2-quart cooking pot.
Turn beef into pot, sprinkle with salt.
Stir over medium heat with a blending fork until all meat changes color.
Add onions and celery, mix well.
Cover and cook over medium heat 2 to 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and liquid and all seasonings, mixing well.
Bring to a boil; cover.
Turn heat low and simmer gently for 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add kidney beans and beef broth.
Simmer over low heat 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet and savory meatballs
directions: Mix
beef, crumbs, onion, egg and garlic.
Shape into 16 meatballs.
In
skillet brown meatballs in shortening; pour off fat.
Add remaining ingredients except for rice.
Cook over low heat 20
minutes or until done.
Stir now and then.
Serve with rice.

title: glazed chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix dressing, soup mix and preserves in a large bowl.
Dip chicken parts into mixture and coat well. Place on foil-lined pan, pour remaining mixture over chicken. Bake for 1/2 hour on each side, turn once more and raise temperature of oven to 375°.
Bake for another 1/2 hour.
During this time glaze should thicken.

title: bachelor's quarters
directions: You will need a can opener, pot with cover, spoon, toaster, knife and a clean plate.

title: black skillet apple cake
directions: Into a black skillet, sift the flour, baking powder, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, cloves and sugar.
Combine the oil, egg, pecans and apples.
Stir together and bake in oven at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: crabmeat melts
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Mix all ingredients except crackers.
Top each cracker with 1 tablespoon of the crabmeat mixture.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Makes 36.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Drain 1 cup juice from pineapple.
Heat with 1 cup of water to boiling point, then pour over jello and mix.
Add cream cheese, mayonnaise and marshmallows.
Mix well with egg beater.
Add crushed pineapple and pecans.
Mix well and chill.

title: french toast casserole
directions: Generously butter a 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish.
Cut bread in 1-inch thick slices.
Arrange in single layer in prepared dish.

title: sicilian pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions; drain.
In a large skillet, simmer oil, garlic, onion and parsley until tender. Combine tomato paste and water.
Add the tomato puree, wine and seasonings.
Continue to simmer 5 to 7 minutes.
Add peppers. Simmer an additional 2 minutes until tender.
Pour over pasta and blend.
Chill approximately 1 to 2 hours.
Garnish with black olives.
Serve cold.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Mix and sift flour, baking powder and salt; stir in 1/2 cup nuts.
Melt shortening.
Add brown sugar and cook slowly until sugar melts.
Stir constantly.
Beat in thoroughly eggs, then vanilla.
Stir in flour mixture.
Turn into greased shallow pan (7 x 11 x 1-inch).
Spread 1/2-inch thick.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cut in squares while warm.
Yields 28 squares.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef.
Add taco mix, water and olives.
Then simmer for 5 minutes.
Form crust by pressing unbaked rolls in pie plate. Sprinkle 1 cup of chips over crust.
Spoon in meat mixture. Spread with sour cream; cover with rest of cheese and rest of chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.
Serve with lettuce and tomato.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray 9 x 13-inch pan with Pam.
Sprinkle onion soup over bottom of pan.
Add rice.
Lay chicken over top of rice.
Dilute chicken soup with water and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Uncover and bake 30 minutes to brown chicken.
The recipe may be altered by adding more rice and soup if desired.
In addition, mushroom soup may be used.
Pour some soup directly on the rice or it will not cook.

title: moist 'n crispy chicken
directions: Place crushed cereal, paprika, salt and pepper in large plastic food bag.
Shake to blend well.
Brush chicken on all sides with mayonnaise.
Place one piece at a time in bag.
Shake to coat well.
Place on rack in broiler pan.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 45 minutes or until golden brown.

title: twice baked potato
directions: Wash potatoes; pat dry.
Prick each potato with fork.
Bake on a rack at 400° for 1 hour or until potatoes are done.
Cut a thin slice from top of each potato; scoop out pulp into a bowl.
Mash potato pulp with the hot milk until fluffy.
Beat in butter and green onions.
Add seasonings.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Add to potato mix.
Spoon potato mixture into shells.
Sprinkle with cheeses.
Place potatoes on baking sheet.
Bake at 375° until cheeses are melted.

title: blackberry cake
directions: Combine cake mix and Jell-O.
Add eggs, oil and wine, mixing well.
Grease 9 x 13 pan.
Pour mixture into pan and bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: crab dip
directions: Soften cheese to room temperature.
Drain and rinse crab and sprinkle with the lemon juice.
Stir all ingredients together. Press into a bowl; chill.
Loosen and invert onto large plate. Surround with crackers and serve.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Separate egg yolks and heat in double boiler.
Make thick paste of flour and water.
Thin if necessary so it will pour. Beat yolks and thickening together.
Add sugar, cocoa and salt. Add milk.
Mix and cook in a double boiler until stiff, stirring constantly.
Pour into baked pie crust. Spread whipped egg whites on top and brown.

title: buttermilk pancakes
directions: Mix together all ingredients.
Heat griddle; grease generous (medium hot).
When bubbles begin to form, turn and brown other side.
(Makes 6 medium size pancakes.)

title: scotch chocolate cake and icing
directions: Combine flour and sugar in a mixing bowl, mixing well.
In a saucepan, put margarine, Crisco, cocoa and water.
Bring to a rapid boil and then pour over flour and sugar, mixing gradually.
Put soda in buttermilk.
Add to the eggs and vanilla.
Beat slightly. Add to other ingredients.
Mix and turn into an 11 x 16 greased and floured pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Make icing 5 minutes before cake is done and pour hot icing over cake.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Peel, slice and dice eggplant.
Boil until tender, then drain. Place eggplant in 2-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Brown bacon and onions together.
Drain off excess drippings.
Add tomato soup, stirring over medium heat.
Add cheese.
When melted, pour over eggplant.
Add croutons on top. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: In large kettle, cover shanks with water.
Heat to boiling. Add bay leaves and peppercorns.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 1 3/4 hours, or until meat on shanks is tender.
Remove shanks from stock; cut meat from shanks into 1/2-inch cubes.
Let stock cool slightly.
Skim fat from surface.
Strain stock into large kettle. Add meat and remaining ingredients; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for about 20 minutes, or until carrots are tender.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350° for about 5 minutes.
Gradually add sugar and salt to beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla.
Fold in chocolate chips and nuts.
Line a cookie sheet with foil.
Drop cookies from a large teaspoon onto the cookie sheet.
Place in oven and turn off heat.
Remove when oven is completely cooled.

title: low-fat lasagna
directions: Mix spaghetti sauce and tomato sauce together.
Layer spaghetti sauce mixture, noodles and cottage cheese in that order. Repeat until four complete layers have been made.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: blackberry apple pie
directions: Roll out crust.
Mix together carefully the apples, blackberries, sugar and cornstarch.
Sprinkle with lemon juice. Add to pie shell.
Dot with butter.
Add top shell; brush with egg and milk.
Bake at 375° for 50 minutes.
While hot, sprinkle with sugar.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in greased casserole at 325° for 1 hour.

title: chicken, cabbage and noodles
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove skin and debone chicken. Cut up cabbage and boil in broth from chicken along with noodles. Add cut up chicken when noodles are done.
Good stew!!

title: cheese krispies
directions: Brown sausage and ground beef; drain.
In saucepan, melt cheese and add the meat to it.
Stir in remaining ingredients; cook for 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Cover; store in refrigerator until serving time.
When ready to serve, spread on cocktail rye and cook on ungreased cookie sheet at 400° for approximately 10 minutes.
Makes approximately 72 slices.

title: mini chip brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in saucepan; stir in brown sugar.
Remove from heat; pour into small mixer bowl.
Cool.
Beat egg and vanilla into cooled mixture.
Add flour and salt, mixing just until well blended.
Stir in mini chips.
Spoon into greased 8 or 9-inch square pan.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes or until brownie begins to pull away from edges of pan.
Cool; frost if desired. Cut into squares.
Yields 16 brownies.

title: kathryn's apple pudding
directions: Mound apples in buttered 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with orange juice.
Combine sugar, flour, spices and salt.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Sprinkle over apples.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes or until apples are tender and topping is crisp.
Makes 6 servings.
Best served warm topped with vanilla ice cream.

title: spicy chicken and pasta
directions: Cut the sausage into slices.
Put the oil in a saucepan over medium heat.
Brown the sausage.
Slice the onion, add to the pan and cook until soft, about 5 minutes.
Chop the garlic, add and cook 2 minutes.
Drain the tomatoes, chop and stir along with the basil, thyme, salt and pepper.
Simmer, stirring occasionally, for about 20 minutes.
Cut the chicken across the grain, making 1/2-inch strips.
Pit and quarter the olives.
Add chicken, olives, parsley and red pepper and simmer gently for 10 minutes. Season to taste with salt and pepper.
Just before serving, boil the pasta and drain it.
Serve pasta topped with the sauce.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread rolls on cookie sheet.
Cook.
Mix 1 package Ranch dressing with cheese.
Cover cooked rolls with softened cream cheese.
Sprinkle Lawry's seasoned salt over all.

title: tang salad
directions: Mix well and Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: beef stroganoff casserole with biscuit topping
directions: Brown meat and onion with seasonings in a large skillet.
Add soup and milk; simmer 10 minutes.
Add sour cream and vegetables. Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Put casserole dish in 350° oven while preparing biscuits.
Remove from oven.
Arrange biscuits on top of mixture.
Bake until biscuits are done.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mediterranean chicken
directions: Heat margarine in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat until melted.
Cook garlic, onion and chicken in margarine until chicken is brown on both sides.
Stir in remaining ingredients; reduce heat.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes or until juice of chicken is no longer pink when centers of thickest pieces are cut.
Yields 6 servings.

title: raisin cake
directions: Put washed raisins into a saucepan with the cold water; boil for 5 minutes.
Cool and drain liquid into a measuring cup; add water to equal 1 c., if necessary.
Cream together sugar and butter.
Sift together flour, cinnamon, cloves and salt.
Dissolve the baking powder and baking soda in the reserved raisin liquid. Mix all ingredients together and add nuts, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 20-25 minutes.

title: karo krazy krunch
directions: Mix nuts and popped corn in a large bowl. Set aside.
In saucepan, combine sugar, butter and Karo. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly, over medium heat.
Boil until mixture reaches 300° on candy thermometer (hard crack stage). Add vanilla and stir.
Pour over popped corn, stirring to coat.
Quickly spread onto a cookie sheet to cool.
Break apart when cooled.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine the first 4 ingredients and form into small meatballs. Brown.
Combine cornstarch, soy sauce, vinegar, water, sugar and pineapple juice.
Cook until thickened.
Add meatballs, green pepper and pineapple.
Heat through and serve.

title: fried biscuits
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Add other ingredients and let dough rise.
Work into biscuits and drop into fat.
This recipe will make about 7 dozen biscuits.
They can be frozen individually and stored in bags.
When you work them up, don't let the biscuits rise too high.
The fat should be slightly hotter than 350°.
If fat should be too hot, the biscuits will be soggy in the center.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Store in jar with screw lid in refrigerator until needed.

title: basil cheese spread
directions: In a food processor blend cream cheese, goat cheese and butter.
Line
a
quart souffle dish with damp cheesecloth, allowing
it
to hang over the sides.
Spread about 1/4 of the cheese
mixture
in
the
souffle dish, followed by 1/3 of the pesto.
Repeat
with
remaining
cheese and pesto, ending with cheese.
Fold
ends
of
cheesecloth
over top and smooth with fingers.
Chill 3 hours
or
until	firm.
Unfold cheesecloth. Press pine nuts around
sides
and	garnish with basil leaves. Refrigerate, cheese keeps 7 to 10 days.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken breasts; cool and cut in bite size pieces.
Set aside.
Crush 3/4 stack Ritz crackers and line bottom of a greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Place the chicken pieces on top of crackers.
Mix the soup and sour cream and pour mixture on top. Top with another 3/4 stack of Ritz crackers.
Melt the butter and mix with poppy seed.
Pour on top.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: shrimpbalaya
directions: In large skillet, melt butter and saut green pepper and sausage until cooked halfway, then add chicken.
Cook until meats are done.
With slotted spoon, remove the meat from pan, letting the drippings drain back into the pan; set aside.
Add flour to make a thickening, then stir in enough milk to make a thin gravy. Add the shrimp to the skillet along with the meat and any juice it may have.
Cook until the shrimp turn pink, about 10 minutes.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve on the noodles.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Pull off about 10 leaves of cabbage; wilt in very hot water. Take raw hamburger and chop up.
Add onion, salt and pepper.
Add rice and mix.
Take cabbage leaf; put ball of hamburger mixture in leaf and add Dash, then roll.
Place toothpick to hold roll together.
Place in bottom of pan.
Cook over medium heat 30 minutes with water just covering.
Add potatoes, whole and peeled. Sprinkle with Dash.
Cover and cook until potatoes are done.
Add juice or sauce and warm.

title: broccoli and ham casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Saute onion in margarine.
Mix with the rest of the ingredients.
Mix together.
Pour into greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: split levels
directions: In a microwave safe bowl, melt chocolate, cream cheese and milk on high for approx. 3 minutes.
Add seeds, stir and set aside.
In a separate bowl combine flour, baking powder, salt, sugar, butter, egg and almond extract.
Spread and press 1/2 of this mixture in the bottom of a 9 x 9 inch pan.
Spread chocolate mixture on top. Sprinkle remaining dry mixture on top of chocolate.
Bake at 375° for 20 - 25 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: tuna waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle apples with lemon juice.
Combine all ingredients. Mix well.
Chill.
May be served on lettuce leaf.

title: czechoslovakian cake(bar cookie)
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients.
Spread 2/3 of the paste in well-greased 9 1/2 x 13-inch pan, then spread on preserves.
Drop rest of paste over preserves so that preserves show through.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar. Cut into squares.

title: peach upside-down cake
directions: Drain peaches. Spread softened butter in bottom of deep, square pan 9x9. Pack brown sugar evenly on top of butter. Arrange peaches, cup side down on sugar mixture. Lay cherries in uniform pattern between peach halves. Cream shortening, add sugar gradually, creaming thoroughly. Blend in well-beaten eggs and flavoring. Stir in sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, beginning and ending with dry ingredients. Pour batter carefully over fruit. Bake in 350 degree oven about 1 hour. Loosen sides of cake with spatula and turn out on pan immediately, allowing pan to rest over cake a few seconds so the syrup will drain. Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: rhubarb custard pie
directions: Cut rhubarb into one-inch pieces.
Beat eggs, milk, sugar, flour, cinnamon and vanilla just until well blended.
Stir in rhubarb.
Pour into pastry lined pie pan.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer lettuce, peas, onion, eggs, bacon and cheese in this order.
Then top with mayonnaise.
Toss when ready to serve.

title: dirt cake
directions: Put cookies in food processor or blender and crush until mixture looks like dirt.
Set aside.
Combine margarine, cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Mix pudding and milk according to package directions.
Add to cream cheese mixture.
Fold in Cool Whip. Layer cookies, cream mixture, cookies, cream mixture, etc. in deep glass bowl.
End with cookie layer on top.
May put gummy worms on top.

title: boiled white icing
directions: In top of double boiler put all ingredients-bring water to boiling and beat egg whites 5 to 7 minutes until peaks form.
Take off burner but leave over water and add 10 marshmallows or 1 c small marshmallows beating until melted. Can be used on layer cake.

title: grandma blaschke's krist cookies
directions: Mix well to make a good stiff cookie dough.
Pinch off pieces the size of walnut or drop by teaspoon on cookie sheet.
Sprinkle with a few drops of water and sugar on each or use milk instead of water.
Bake at 350° until light brown.

title: american lasagna
directions: Alternate cooked noodles, Swiss cheese, cottage cheese, American cheese and meat sauce in a dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: best chocolate fudge
directions: Boil sugar, vanilla, butter and milk for 2 minutes and stir. Turn off heat!
Add marshmallows, cut in small pieces; stir until marshmallows are melted.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and pour out on cookie sheet.
Nuts may be added.

title: chicken broth with enoki mushrooms
directions: Bring stock, chicken (if desired) and ginger to a boil in medium saucepan.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer 10 minutes. Strain through fine sieve and return to pan.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. Garnish with coriander and serve.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Using vegetable shortening, lightly grease a small baking cookie sheet.
In large bowl, sift flour, sugar, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add softened butter and cut into flour mixture using a pastry blender or fork until it's in fine crumbs.
Add raisins and toss.
Pour buttermilk into flour and toss mixture with fork until mixed well.
Using hands, gently gather mixture and press into a ball.
Put ball on a lightly floured board and knead with palms of your hands until dough is smooth (about 1 minute).
Shape into a smooth round ball and place on prepared cookie sheet.
Using hands, flatten dough into a circle (about 1 1/2 inches thick).
Press a large floured knife into center of loaf, halfway through dough.
Repeat at right angle, to divide loaf into quarters.
Sprinkle cinnamon very lightly on top.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Bake until golden brown.
Cool on wire rack and brush top with melted butter while still warm.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together with mixer and pour into an unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake at 375° about 45 minutes, or until firm.

title: dill pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers.
Pack in quart jars.
Place 2 garlic bulbs (this is the little individual bulbs after the big bulb has been peeled), hot pepper and 1 head of dill in each quart jar.
Bring water, vinegar and salt to a rolling boil.
Pour over cukes.
Seal jars.

title: fried rice
directions: Saute margarine, onion, pepper and mushrooms together.
Place in 2-quart casserole.
Add 1 cup uncooked long grain rice, seasoning and broth powder, Gravy Master and water/mushroom liquid.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook sweet potatoes in their jackets in boiling salted water until nearly tender.
Drain, peel and cut in slices about 1/2-inch thick.
Place in a greased shallow baking dish and sprinkle with salt.
Cook together brown sugar, water and butter in a separate pan for several minutes.
Then stir in lemon juice and pour over potatoes.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 20 to 25 minutes, basting occasionally with the syrup.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chilled mustard sauce for stone crab claws
directions: Blend mustard, mayonnaise and A.1. sauce until smooth. Gradually add cream; chill and serve with stone crab claws.
Makes 2 cups.

title: pot roast and gravy
directions: Season roast with seasoned salt, onion powder, seasoned pepper and garlic powder. Brown roast on both sides in hot olive oil in large Dutch oven. Add 3/4 cup of water, chopped onion, minced garlic, parsley and thyme. Cover and cook slowly for about 3 hours. Remove roast to serving platter. Skim fat. Make gravy.

title: aunt betty's dill pickles
directions: Wash and sterilize jars. Put 1 sprig of dill in bottom of each jar. Pack cucumbers into jars. Bring water, vinegar and salt to a boil and boil for about 5 minutes. Pour over cucumbers and seal.

title: elephant ears
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup water.
Set aside.
Combine salt, sugar and 2 cups flour.
Stir in yeast, 1 cup water, beaten egg and butter.
Beat in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Put cabbage leaves into boiling water until soft; drain.
Mix all ingredients.
Melt 1/2 stick butter in casserole dish.
Divide mixture into equal parts with cabbage leaves.
Roll up; put into baking dish.
Cut up 1/2 stick butter; put on top of rolls.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: sugared pecans
directions: In a large bowl, toss pecans in beaten egg white, coating evenly. Add dry ingredients and toss well. Spread nuts on greased baking sheet, (I cover the sheet with foil and spray the foil with vegetable spray) and bake at 300 degrees for 45 minutes to 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice, water and salt until done. Mix together well and top with a mixture of fresh bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese. Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: old south cucumber lime pickles
directions: Soak clean cucumbers in water and lime mixture in crockery or enamel ware for 12 hours or overnight.
Do not use aluminum ware. Wash 3 times in clean water and soak in fresh ice water for 3 hours.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to a low boil; stir until sugar is dissolved.
Add cucumbers and soak 5 to 6 hours or overnight.
Boil pickles in soaking liquid for 35 minutes.
Fill sterilized quart jars with cucumber slices and pour syrup over cucumbers, leaving 1/2-inch headspace.
Cap each jar when filled.
Process 5 minutes in boiling water bath.
Boiling water should cover jars by 1-inch.
Start processing time when filled jars are placed in rolling boiling water canner with tight fitting lid.
Should be left on high heat during processing. Label.
Store in dry, dark, cool place.

title: sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Put in a greased 9 x 13-inch dish. Sprinkle with cheese.
In separate bowl, mix eggs, milk, Bisquick, onion, salt and pepper.
Beat and pour over sausage and cheese. Bake at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: homemade brown sugar syrup
directions: Mix sugars and water in saucepan.
Cook until mixture will spin a fine thread.
Serve hot with hot pancakes and homemade butter.

title: salmon patties
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the potatoes, salmon, onion, cracker crumbs, parsley, salt, pepper and egg yolk; mix well. Beat egg white until stiff peaks form; fold into salmon mixture. Shape into six patties.
Heat oil in skillet; fry patties over medium heat for 3 to 4 minutes per side or until lightly browned.

title: sweet and sour pork
directions: Combine soy sauce, ginger, salt and garlic.
Pour over pork and marinate 30 minutes. Dredge pork in cornstarch.
Cook (in oil), drain.
Cook vinegar, ketchup, brown sugar, Worcestershire and pepper sauce to a boil.
Add green pepper and onions.
Add tomatoes and pineapple, 2 tablespoons cornstarch and water. Thicken and pour over hot pork.
Serve with rice.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O and water; chill until thick.
Stir in other ingredients.
Put in muffin tins or paper muffin cups. Refrigerate until firm.

title: carrot pennies
directions: Slice carrots into pennies.
Cook until fork-tender.
Chop pepper and onion and combine with remaining ingredients.
Add to drained carrots.
Let marinate several hours and serve cold.

title: sweet potato supreme
directions: Combine all ingredients; spoon into 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish.

title: breakfast on-the-go drink
directions: Place can of pineapple (with all the juice), strawberries and ice cubes in blender.
Cover and set it on "chop" for about 5 seconds.
Add sliced up banana and yogurt; blend on "liquefy" or "stir" for about 10 seconds, until smooth.
Add sweetener to taste and blend 2 more seconds.
Serves 2.

title: aunt lela burton's pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Grease and flour 10-inch tube cake pan. Cream margarine, Crisco and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time, and beat until creamy.
Add flavoring, salt and flour.
Beat until creamy.
Bake for about 1 1/2 hours or until tests done. Cake will freeze well.
Add an extra egg if more moisture needed.

title: pumpkin ring
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour angel food cake pan. Beat all ingredients (except glaze) on low speed for 30 seconds. Beat on medium speed for 3 minutes.

title: meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients together. Shape meat balls. Place on baking sheet and bake until no longer pink. Simmer barbecue sauce and meatballs in crock-pot.

title: spaghetti and master meat sauce
directions: Add Italian seasoning and package of spaghetti season mix to two cups Master Meat Sauce.
Heat and mix with 4 cups of hot, cooked, drained spaghetti.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs, zucchini and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients and nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour for 1 big loaf pan. Adjust time for smaller loaves.
Done when toothpick inserted in center comes clean.

title: marinated grilled chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and marinate overnight or several hours in refrigerator.
Grill over slow coals about 1 hour or until done, turning frequently and brushing with marinade.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook and drain broccoli.
Place in casserole (sprayed with Pam).
Heat soup, cheese and oleo until melted.
Pour over broccoli and cover with croutons.
Heat in oven until croutons brown a little.
If you don't like croutons, you may use Ritz crackers or Pepperidge stuffing mix instead.

title: savory cornish hens
directions: Remove giblet packs; wash hens and pat dry.
Cut crusts from bread; cut into 1/2-inch cubes.
Place on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden, stirring occasionally; remove from oven. Combine parsley, salt, pepper and poultry seasoning; set aside.
In heavy skillet, melt butter.
Add onions and livers; cook until livers are lightly browned and onions are tender.
Remove and chop livers.
Add livers, onions and butter from pan to bread cubes; toss to mix well.
Salt and pepper hens lightly.
Pack tightly with stuffing; truss.
Place in oven baking dish, breast side up.
Brush with melted butter; roast at 375°.
Turn every 15 minutes; baste with butter and pan juices.
Cook a total of 50 to 60 minutes, until juices run clear when knife tip is inserted in hen.
Serve hot.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, pepper, pimientos and 1/2 can Durkee French fried onions.
Pour into a 1-quart casserole.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs and pumpkin together, then add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Bake in 2 (9 x 13-inch) greased pans at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool and frost.

title: truffle cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed.
Make pudding as directed.
Layer crumbled cake, strawberries, pudding, Cool Whip and Heath bars. Repeat layers.

title: glazed carrot, vicky
directions: Peel and slice carrots approximately 1/4-inch thick.
Place carrots in saucepan or straight sided saute pan.
Add enough water to barely cover carrots.
Add butter, sugar, salt and nutmeg. Bring to a boil and reduce to simmer.
Stir occasionally.
Simmer carrots until almost all water has evaporated and carrots are tender.
Toss carrots to coat with glaze.
Garnish with chopped parsley, if desired.

title: butter cheese cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix with a spoon, cake mix, softened margarine, 2 eggs and 1 cup chopped pecans.
Batter will be thick. Pat mixture into a buttered, floured 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Mix with mixer powdered sugar, 2 eggs and cream cheese.
Then pour over the mixture in pan and bake at 300° to 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Do not expect to test the doneness with a toothpick.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Prepare Jello according to package directions.
Let it set up, then whip.
Add all other ingredients.
Chill.

title: great-grandmother's pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Heat, stirring constantly until thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Cover with meringue and brown.

title: oven fried potatoes
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until tender.

title: peanut butter sandwiches baked in custard
directions: This diet is designed to help you cope with stress buildup during the day.

title: upside-down blueberry coffee cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Add milk and egg; stir just enough to moisten the dry ingredients.
Spread topping in bottom of greased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with batter.
Bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Layer as listed, except mayonnaise and cheese.
Mix mayonnaise and cheese, then spread on top.
Cover tightly and refrigerate overnight.

title: apple bars
directions: Place half of
Gilge
pie
crust
in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Sprinkle pie
crust with crushed corn flakes.
Combine apples, sugar and
cinnamon.
Pour over pie crust.
Cover with rest of pie crust;
prick steam holes.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes. Drizzle with confectioners sugar icing.
Delicious with cheese as well!

title: southern fried apple pies
directions: Mix all together and set aside to cool.

title: sweet and sour lentils
directions: Combine water and lentils; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1/2 hour.
Add chopped onion and cook 15 minutes more.
Add remaining ingredients.
Add more water if lentils look dry.
Continue to simmer for 10 minutes.
If the lentils are not tender, add a little more water and soak a few more minutes. Serve over rice, bulgur or millet.

title: company casserole
directions: Brown beef, salt and pepper.
Mix together soups, sour cream, peas, pimientos and cooked noodles.
Add to meat mixture.
Pour into baking dish and sprinkle with bread crumbs or grated cheese. Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until bubbly.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: *Some suggestions: broccoli, carrots, cauliflower, tomatoes and green onion.

title: believe it or not pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops; place in baking dish.
Mix Coke and ketchup together; pour over pork chops.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Believe it or not:
This is delicious!

title: inexpensive fruitcake
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Simmer gently for 20 minutes the raisins, dates, sugar, water and shortening.
Cool.
Sift together and stir in dry ingredients.
Mix in nuts.
Pour into two well-greased and floured loaf pans (8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch).
Bake for 1 1/2 to 1 3/4 hours.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Stir all ingredients to a soft dough.
Gently smooth dough on floured, cloth-covered board into a ball.
Knead five times.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: Sift first 3 ingredients together. Then mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured 11 x 7 x 1-inch baking dish. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Five minutes before it is finished cooking, mix topping together.

title: spinach and cheese baked ziti
directions: In large pot, cook ziti as package directs; cook spinach and drain.
Squeeze to remove excess moisture.
In a large bowl, combine spinach, Ricotta, eggs, Parmesan, pepper and nutmeg. Preheat oven to 375°.
Drain ziti and return to pot.
Add spaghetti sauce and oregano.
Place half the ziti in a 12 1/2 x 8 1/2-inch clear shallow baking dish.
Add all of the spinach mixture and half the Mozzarella.
Top with remaining ziti and Mozzarella and cover with foil.
Bake 25 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes or until bubbly.
Let stand 10 minutes, then serve.
Serves 8.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Saute first five vegetables in 1/2 stick margarine.
Combine undiluted soup and sour cream.
Mix until smooth and add carrots and sauteed vegetables, mixing lightly.
Combine stuffing mix and melted margarine.
Spread 1/2 of stuffing mixture over bottom of greased 12 x 7-inch baking dish.
Spoon vegetable mixture on top and sprinkle with remainder of stuffing.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: texas yum-yum cake
directions: Mix and spread in 9 x 13-inch pan; bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: zucchini jam
directions: Boil zucchini, sugar and pineapple for 10 minutes.
Add Jell-O; boil 2 minutes longer, until it starts to thicken.

title: pumpkin chiffon pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water.
Set aside.
Beat egg yolks.
Add evaporated milk, pumpkin, 1/2 cup brown sugar, salt and spices. Cook over medium heat 3 to 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Add gelatin mixture, stirring until dissolved.
Cool. Beat egg whites until stiff but not dry.
Add rest of sugar.
Fold into pumpkin mixture.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts. Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: Combine in large bowl the condensed milk and wafers.
Add pudding mix.
Beat well.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream. Spoon 1 cup pudding mixture into 2 1/2-quart glass serving bowl. Top with 1/3 each of the wafers, bananas and pudding.
Repeat layering twice.
End with pudding.
Chill.
Garnish.
Refrigerate.

title: gulliver's creamed corn
directions: Combine all ingredients except flour and butter.
Bring to a boil and simmer 5 minutes.
Blend flour and butter in another pan, then pour into the big mixture.
Blend well and let thicken.
If you wish, just put 1 tablespoon of flour first and see if thickens.
If not, then add the second tablespoon.
Bring to the desired consistency.
If you like corn, this will melt in your mouth.

title: enchilada stack-ups
directions: Combine tomato sauce, chilies and seasoning in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes. Combine cheese and onions.
Mix lightly.
Place tortilla in paper towel and heat slightly in microwave to soften.
Place 1 tortilla in large casserole dish or large skillet with 2 tablespoons sauce and 1/2 cup cheese mixture.
Repeat layers ending with a tortilla on top.
Top with remaining sauce.
Bake at 350° 25 minutes. Sprinkle with remaining cheese mixture.
Continue baking until cheese is melted.
Cut in wedges.
Serve.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Mix margarine, sugar, pumpkin and eggs together.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix well and drop by spoonfuls onto slightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° until golden brown (about 8 to 10 minutes).
Remove from cookie sheet and cool.

title: crazy chocolate cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in ungreased square baking pan.
Make 3 holes; pour oil in one, vinegar in one and vanilla in the other. Pour water over all.
Mix well with a fork.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: chinese casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Combine hamburger and remaining ingredients except noodles and pour into casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Top with noodles and bake for 5 minutes. Serves 6.

title: 3 step cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer until well blended. Add eggs and mix again. When well blended, pour mixture into crust and bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool in refrigerator 3 hours or overnight.

title: chow mein noodle cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips.
Add peanut butter.
When soft, add chopped peanuts and noodles.
Mix thoroughly.
Dip out with teaspoon and lay on wax paper until cold.

title: lemon cake squares(yield: 24 large squares)
directions: 1. Preheat oven to 350°.

title: frosty eggnog
directions: Beat eggs well. Add sugar and salt; blend well. Add milk, Cool Whip, vanilla and nutmeg. Blend thoroughly and chill.
May be served from a punch bowl or stored in a milk carton in the refrigerator until desired. Shake well before serving.

title: convenient mashed potato casserole
directions: Boil, drain and mash potatoes with all ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Put in long casserole dish and top with bacon bits, paprika, parsley flakes and pepper. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cocoa cream pie
directions: Mix cocoa, cornstarch, yolks of 3 eggs, sugar, salt and milk in saucepan on medium to low heat.
Cook until thick; remove from heat and add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: cheese enchiladas
directions: Sauce:
Combine tomato sauce and water in a skillet.
Season with cumin and chili powder to taste.
Heat to a low boil to mix flavors.
Reduce to a simmer.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add all ingredients and mix with enough water to mix good.
Cook to desired.

title: punch
directions: Combine pineapple juice, lemonade and orange juice.
Add ginger ale just before serving.
Add maraschino cherries or sherbet, if desired.

title: angel delight cake
directions: Break angel food cake into small pieces and place in a long baking dish.
Pour cooked pudding over cake pieces and cover with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle flaked coconut over Cool Whip.
Sprinkle red cinnamon drops on top of cake for festive occasion.

title: sausage dip
directions: Melt cheese in a double boiler.
Brown the sausage and drain. Saute onions and bell pepper in butter.
Mix all ingredients and heat in crock-pot.

title: walnut dream bars
directions: With a pastry blender or two knives, cut the butter or margarine into 1 cup of the flour and 1/4 cup of the brown sugar, until mixture is the consistency of coarse cornmeal, as in pie crust.
Pat this mixture firmly into an ungreased 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan and bake in moderate oven, 350°, for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Combine all ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Add remainder of cheese just before serving.
Important: Cover with foil before baking.

title: pepper steak
directions: Brown meat slowly in hot fat about 15 minutes.
Add onion and garlic the last few minutes.
Season with salt and pepper. Dissolve bouillon cube in hot water; add to meat.
Cover and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Add tomatoes and green pepper.
Cook 10 minutes longer.
Combine cornstarch, cold water and soy sauce and stir into meat mixture.
Bring to boil, cook and stir 5 minutes longer.
Remove garlic.
Serve with hot noodles.
Can use round steak sprinkled with tenderizer and floured.
Adjust cooking time.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except cake mix, oleo and nuts, together. Pour into a large, ungreased baking dish.
Top with yellow cake mix; drizzle melted oleo over the top.
Sprinkle on the nuts. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and no longer.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fry hamburger; drain.
Add rest of ingredients.
Heat through. Serve with taco chips, sour cream and cheese.

title: coconut bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt; set aside. In a large bowl, combine sugar, oil, eggs and coconut extract.

Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk; stir just until moistened. Fold in coconut and nuts. Pour into two greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until breads test done. Cool 10 minutes in pans before removing to a wire rack to cool completely. Yield: 2 loaves.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Heat pineapple with Jell-O until dissolved. Cool completely. Add buttermilk, drained pineapple and Cool Whip.
Mix thoroughly. Add nuts.
